abstract: National Association of Realtors reports sales of previously owned homes in United States rose 1.2 percent in February to annual rate of 4.88 million units; slow home sales are sign economy slowed sharply in first quarter.
lead_paragraph: The sluggish home sales are a sign that economic activity slowed in the first quarter.

headline.main: Sales of Existing Homes Rose 1.2% in February
